urally constructed nature of age can we expose its ubiquitous and stealthy influence.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 4aCultural Studies : Gerontology/Aging Studies. 4aHistory : History. 4aLiterature : English Literature. 4aLiterature : Nineteenth-Century Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978079147726740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791477267423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791477267/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles